-LET'S GO, ESE!

28:54.036 --> 28:56.691
-HECTOR: HEY, ESE,
PUT THE GUN AWAY.

28:56.822 --> 28:58.824
PULGA, MAN, WHAT'S
WRONG WITH YOU, MAN?

28:58.954 --> 29:01.043
DON'T DO THIS, DON'T
SHOOT HIM, HOLMES.

29:07.702 --> 29:09.660
-HEY, HEY, HEY,
WHERE YOU GOING, ESE?

29:10.313 --> 29:12.272
HEY, GET BACK
IN THE CAR, ESE.

29:14.665 --> 29:16.667
LEAVE HIM, FOOL. HE'S DEAD.

29:17.451 --> 29:18.191
-HECTOR: MAYBE NOT.

29:18.321 --> 29:19.627
-DAMN.

29:19.758 --> 29:22.108
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

29:52.616 --> 29:55.402
-COME ON, MAN. LET ME FEEL IT.

29:55.532 --> 30:00.711
[SIRENS BLARING]

30:07.631 --> 30:10.025
[COUGHING]
YEAH.

30:10.591 --> 30:12.201
YOU'RE BREATHING, MAN.

30:19.992 --> 30:21.471
I GOT HIS HEART STARTED, MAN.

30:22.516 --> 30:24.474
I DID CPR, HE WASN'T BREATHING.

30:24.605 --> 30:28.565
[SIRENS BLARING]

30:42.188 --> 30:45.060
-LOOK, CODY KNOWS AND
NEELY SUSPECTS, ALRIGHT?

30:45.191 --> 30:47.802
WORKING SIDE BY SIDE LIKE
THIS IS DRIVING ME CRAZY.

30:47.933 --> 30:49.630
WHY DON'T WE JUST
TELL THEM ALL?

30:49.760 --> 30:52.720
-OR, END IT NOW BEFORE
ANYONE GETS HURT.

30:53.895 --> 30:55.157
-ANYONE LIKE WHO?

30:55.636 --> 30:58.639
-LIKE US.

30:59.770 --> 31:01.033
-YOU CAN'T BE SERIOUS.

31:01.163 --> 31:02.599
YOU MEAN JUST END
THE WHOLE THING,

31:02.730 --> 31:03.687
AND PRETEND LIKE NONE
OF THIS NEVER HAPPENED.

31:04.950 --> 31:06.168
-I JUST...

31:06.690 --> 31:08.301
I'M JUST AFRAID THAT
IF WE WORK TOGETHER

31:08.431 --> 31:10.172
AND HAVE A RELATIONSHIP,

31:10.303 --> 31:12.566
THAT AT SOME POINT ONE OF
THEM IS GOING TO HAVE TO END.

31:12.696 --> 31:14.220
-NEITHER HAS TO END.

31:15.264 --> 31:17.527
SAM, THERE'S NO REASON
WE CAN'T HAVE BOTH.

31:18.528 --> 31:19.529
-THAT'S WHAT ADAM SAID.

31:20.356 --> 31:21.967
-ADAM? YOUR EX?

31:24.752 --> 31:26.797
-IT WAS THE SAME SITUATION.

31:26.928 --> 31:28.582
WE WORKED TOGETHER
FIVE DAYS A WEEK.

31:28.712 --> 31:30.149
WE STARTED
A BUSINESS TOGETHER,

31:31.890 --> 31:33.239
AND THEN WE FELL IN LOVE.

31:33.369 --> 31:36.590
WHEN THINGS GOT
COMPLICATED AND CONFUSED,

31:36.720 --> 31:40.246
AND SIX MONTHS LATER,
I SOLD HIM HALF OF MY BUSINESS

31:40.376 --> 31:42.770
AND RAN BACK HERE TO THE
BEACH JUST TO GET AWAY.

31:45.860 --> 31:48.471
MITCH, WE DIDN'T WANT TO
HURT EACH OTHER, BUT WE DID.

31:54.477 --> 31:55.957
-THAT WON'T HAPPEN WITH US.

31:59.787 --> 32:02.311
-I CAME HERE TO GET
AWAY FROM COMPLICATIONS,

32:02.442 --> 32:05.706
AND NOW I FEEL LIKE I'M
RIGHT BACK WHERE I STARTED.

32:08.187 --> 32:09.971
-YOU'RE WITH A DIFFERENT, MAN.

32:11.581 --> 32:15.977
SAM, I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU.

32:17.587 --> 32:19.850
I NEVER THOUGHT I'D
FEEL THIS WAY AGAIN.

32:21.374 --> 32:22.723
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE IT.

32:24.725 --> 32:26.074
-I DON'T EITHER.

32:34.082 --> 32:36.215
-YOU KNOW, HONEY, WHEN I WAS 17,
I COULD'VE BOUGHT A DRESS

32:36.345 --> 32:38.043
FOR WHAT IT COSTS
TO CLEAN ONE TODAY.

32:38.173 --> 32:39.392
-BETTER CLOSE THE DOOR,

32:39.522 --> 32:40.828
THERE'S A LOT OF
BAD DUDES OUT THERE.

32:40.959 --> 32:43.135
-HECTOR!
-HOW'D YOU KNOW WHERE WE LIVED?

32:43.265 --> 32:44.832
-NOT, MANY HOMIES
LIVE IN MALIBU.

32:44.963 --> 32:46.312
-HOW DID YOU GET IN HERE?

32:46.442 --> 32:48.096
-I TOOK A CLASS IN SCHOOL.

32:48.227 --> 32:49.924
LOCKPICKING 101.

32:50.055 --> 32:51.491
-MAN, WHAT'S UP WITH YOU?

32:51.621 --> 32:53.667
YOU SHINED US OUT THERE,
NOW YOU SHOW UP HERE?

32:53.797 --> 32:55.408
-I GOT
A LITTLE TROUBLE, MAN.

32:55.538 --> 32:57.932
PULGA, HE SHOT AT THAT
GUY WHO HE DID CPR WITH.

32:58.063 --> 32:59.238
-AY, DIOS!

32:59.368 --> 33:00.804
-HE HIT HIS ARM,
AND HE MISSED HIM,

33:00.935 --> 33:02.850
BUT HE CRASHED INTO
A TELEPHONE POLE.

33:02.981 --> 33:04.330
-WAS HE KILLED?

33:04.460 --> 33:06.549
-I THINK SO, BUT I
DID THAT CPR STUFF,

33:06.680 --> 33:07.637
AND HE CAME BACK.

33:09.378 --> 33:12.338
HIS HEART STARTED BEATING,
HE JUST CAME BACK, MAN.

33:12.468 --> 33:15.123
-WAY TO GO, MAN!
SEE, YOU DID IT.

33:15.254 --> 33:17.778
-YEAH, BUT THE PARAMEDICS
ID'ED ME WITH THE COPS.

33:17.908 --> 33:20.389
MAN, PULGA KNOWS I'M THE
ONLY ONE WHO CAN RAT HIM OUT.

33:21.303 --> 33:23.044
I GOT
A DOUBLE DOSE OF IT, MAN.

33:23.175 --> 33:24.654
EVERYONE'S LOOKING
TO CLOSE ME OUT.

33:26.265 --> 33:28.310
IS IT OKAY
IF I STAY HERE A WHILE?

33:28.441 --> 33:30.051
JUST 'TIL THINGS
GET QUIET OUT THERE.

33:30.182 --> 33:32.923
-AND RUN FOREVER? NO.

33:34.012 --> 33:35.187
-WAIT, WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

33:35.317 --> 33:36.753
-THE POLICE.

33:36.884 --> 33:38.320
HECTOR, YOU'VE GOT TO
TELL THEM THE TRUTH.

33:38.451 --> 33:39.843
-YOU CALLING THE COPS ON ME?

33:39.974 --> 33:41.497
YOU HATE ME THAT MUCH?

33:41.628 --> 33:43.412
-NO, HECTOR,
I LOVE YOU THAT MUCH.

33:47.721 --> 33:49.897
-MANNY: HECTOR, WHERE
ARE YOU GOING, MAN?

33:52.813 --> 33:55.990
[EXCITING MUSIC]

33:59.472 --> 34:01.213
HECTOR, YOU DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING WRONG, MAN.

34:01.343 --> 34:04.303
YOU SAVED THAT GUY'S
LIFE. PULGA'S TOO.

34:04.433 --> 34:06.261
-PULGA? ARE YOU CRAZY?

34:06.392 --> 34:07.828
-IF YOU DIDN'T SAVE
THAT GUY'S LIFE,

34:07.958 --> 34:09.438
PULGA WOULD BE UP
FOR MURDER, MAN.

34:09.569 --> 34:11.571
-LET ME GO, MANNY!
-NO!

34:11.701 --> 34:13.181
-I'LL KILL YOU, MANNY!

34:13.312 --> 34:15.792
-YOU HAVE TO. YOU
DIDN'T DO ANYTHING WRONG.

34:15.922 --> 34:17.011
YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

34:17.141 --> 34:19.100
DO THE RIGHT THING AGAIN.

34:19.231 --> 34:21.797
TURN YOURSELF IN
TO THE POLICE.

34:21.929 --> 34:23.844
IT'S THE RIGHT THING
TO DO, MAN.

34:25.759 --> 34:27.195
THINK ABOUT IT.

34:39.467 --> 34:41.079
-WHAT TIME DOES
HOBIE'S FLIGHT GET IN?

34:41.208 --> 34:44.429
-7:40, ONE OF HIS BUDDIES
IS GOING TO PICK HIM UP.

34:44.560 --> 34:46.127
-WHAT HIS MOM GET
HIM FOR HIS BIRTHDAY?

34:46.257 --> 34:47.955
-SHE SAID SHE GOT HIM
A LAPTOP COMPUTER.

34:48.085 --> 34:49.087
NOT BAD, HUH?

34:49.217 --> 34:51.437
BUT, YOU CAN'T DRIVE IT.

34:53.525 --> 34:55.092
-HOBIE: SEE YOU LATER,
RICK, THANKS FOR THE RIDE.

34:55.223 --> 34:56.616
HEY, DAD!

34:56.746 --> 34:58.270
-MITCH: HEY, MAN,
I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

34:58.400 --> 35:00.707
-MISSED YOU TOO.
HEY, SAM, HOW ARE YOU?

35:00.837 --> 35:02.317
-SAMANTHA: WELCOME HOME.
-GOOD FLIGHT?

35:02.448 --> 35:04.232
-YEAH, IT WAS GREAT.
MOM SENT YOU SOME COOKIES.

35:04.363 --> 35:06.104
-DOUBLE CHOCOLATE CHIP?
-OF COURSE.

35:06.234 --> 35:07.670
CHECK OUT MY NEW
LAPTOP COMPUTER.

35:07.801 --> 35:09.019
-YEAH, SHE TOLD ME.
COME ON, SIT DOWN.

35:10.934 --> 35:13.807
WE GOT YOU SOME NICE PRESENTS,
BUT YOUR BIGGER PRESENT

35:13.937 --> 35:15.548
ARRIVES TOMORROW.

35:15.678 --> 35:17.376
-"ARRIVES"? WHAT
DO YOU MEAN ARRIVES?

35:17.506 --> 35:18.333
WHAT IS IT?

35:19.334 --> 35:21.119
-WELL, YOU'LL JUST
HAVE TO WAIT AND SEE.

35:21.249 --> 35:24.252
I WANT YOU TO BE AT BAYWATCH
TOMORROW MORNING, 10 O'CLOCK.

35:25.035 --> 35:27.037
-SO, THEN I CAN
OPEN THESE NOW--

35:27.168 --> 35:31.825
-BEFORE WE GO INTO THESE,
I JUST WANTED TO HAVE LIKE

35:31.955 --> 35:32.826
A LITTLE MAN-TO-MAN TALK.

35:33.522 --> 35:35.002
[CLEARS THROAT]

35:35.133 --> 35:37.570
ACTUALLY A LITTLE
MAN-AND-WOMAN-TO-MAN TALK.

35:38.223 --> 35:39.354
-SURE, WHAT'S UP?

35:39.485 --> 35:41.530
-WELL, WHILE YOU WERE IN OHIO,

35:41.661 --> 35:44.229
SOME THINGS SORT OF HAPPENED.

35:44.359 --> 35:46.187
-HAPPENED? WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

35:47.884 --> 35:52.889
-WELL, SAM AND I FELL IN LOVE.

35:54.326 --> 35:57.155
-COOL, THAT'S GREAT.
CONGRATULATIONS, YOU GUYS.

35:58.417 --> 36:01.115
-THAT'S IT? I MEAN,
YOU'RE NOT SHOCKED?

36:01.246 --> 36:03.335
-COME ON, DAD, I'M NOT BLIND.

36:03.465 --> 36:05.337
I SAW THIS COMING
A LONG TIME AGO.

36:05.467 --> 36:06.990
-YOU SAW IT COMING?

36:07.121 --> 36:09.515
-SURE, I MEAN YOU GUYS
ARE PERFECT FOR EACH OTHER.

36:09.645 --> 36:12.300
YOU LOVE THE SAME
WORK, SAME FUN.

36:12.431 --> 36:14.172
I MEAN,
YOU GUYS FIT TOGETHER.

36:14.998 --> 36:18.959
BUT I THINK IF THIS
IS GONNA WORK OUT,

36:20.352 --> 36:21.918
ME AND YOU NEED TO
TALK ABOUT SOMETHING,

36:22.049 --> 36:22.919
AND I NEED YOU TO BE HONEST.

36:23.050 --> 36:23.920
-SURE.

36:26.488 --> 36:28.186
-WHAT'S MY PRESENT
THAT'S ARRIVING TOMORROW?

36:28.316 --> 36:32.233
-NO! NO WAY! 10 O'CLOCK, YOU
WAIT TOMORROW. 10 O'CLOCK.

36:32.929 --> 36:35.454
[CHEERFUL MUSIC]

36:51.121 --> 36:53.254
[LAUGHING]

37:02.785 --> 37:06.789
[SERIOUS MUSIC]

37:09.662 --> 37:10.837
-WORKING HARD, LIFEGUARD?

37:10.967 --> 37:12.447
WHO'S GUARDING
YOUR LIFE NOW, ESE?

37:12.578 --> 37:15.276
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?
-I'LL TELL YOU WHAT I WANT.

37:16.625 --> 37:18.453
I WANT YOU TO TAKE A
MESSAGE TO YOUR BOY HECTOR.

37:18.584 --> 37:20.847
AND YOU TELL HIM IF HE
GIVES MY NAME TO THE COPS,

37:20.977 --> 37:23.980
YOUR MAMACITA'S GOING
TO PAY WITH HER LIFE.

37:31.945 --> 37:33.729
-NEELY: ARE YOU OKAY?
-WHAT IS IT?

37:33.860 --> 37:35.165
-YOU'LL FIND OUT, HANG ON.

37:37.298 --> 37:38.865
HEY?

37:38.995 --> 37:41.520
HEY, COME ON WHAT ARE YOU DOING!
THAT'S MY KID'S CAR!

37:41.650 --> 37:44.697
-CAR?
-FOLLOW THAT CAR.

37:44.827 --> 37:46.786
[ACTION-PACKED MUSIC]

37:55.534 --> 37:57.187
GET NEXT TO HIM,
GET NEXT TO HIM.

37:58.319 --> 37:59.929
HE'S TURNING. ALL RIGHT.

38:17.164 --> 38:19.949
CLOSER, CLOSER.
ALRIGHT, HOLD IT STEADY.

38:31.831 --> 38:33.223
TURN IT OFF!

38:35.922 --> 38:38.403
HEY, THAT'S MY SON'S CAR.

38:51.459 --> 38:53.200
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK, PAL?

38:53.331 --> 38:55.202
-THIS IS THE GREATEST CAR
EVER, THANK YOU SO MUCH, GUYS.

38:55.333 --> 38:56.725
-HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
-HOBIE: I LOVE YOU GUYS.

38:56.856 --> 38:58.248
-MAN, YOU DESERVE IT.

38:58.379 --> 38:59.598
NOW LISTEN, YOU'VE
GOT YOUR SEAT BELT ON?

38:59.728 --> 39:01.121
REMEMBER, FOUR ON
THE FLOOR, OKAY.

39:01.251 --> 39:03.036
-DAD, I HAVE MY LICENSE,
I KNOW HOW TO DRIVE.

39:03.166 --> 39:05.168
-OKAY, OKAY, I'M JUST
BEING YOUR DAD HERE.

39:05.299 --> 39:07.910
LOOK, YOU BE CAREFUL, HUH?
THIS THING CAN HAUL.

39:08.041 --> 39:10.565
-PROMISE.
-ALL RIGHT. GO FOR IT.

39:10.696 --> 39:12.219
[HOOTING]

39:17.224 --> 39:19.226
-HEY, HEY, HEY!
SLOW DOWN! SLOW DOWN!

39:23.796 --> 39:26.407
I THINK THIS IS THE BIGGEST
MISTAKE I'VE EVER MADE.

39:26.538 --> 39:28.757
-AH, YOU THINK TOO
MUCH, HE'S GONNA BE FINE.

39:29.236 --> 39:30.368
AND SO ARE WE.

39:30.933 --> 39:32.892
-YOU READY?
-READY AS I'LL EVER BE.

39:33.022 --> 39:34.676
-ALRIGHT, LET'S DO IT.

39:44.512 --> 39:46.601
-HEY, NEELY, YOU GOT A MINUTE?
-SURE.

39:47.472 --> 39:52.041
-SAM TELLS ME THAT YOU THINK
WE ARE HAVING AN AFFAIR.

39:52.172 --> 39:57.351
-WELL, YOU KNOW I JUST
THOUGHT THAT MAYBE YOU--

39:57.482 --> 39:58.396
-WE'RE NOT.

39:59.832 --> 40:00.876
-TOLD YOU.

40:01.007 --> 40:02.051
-OH.

40:02.661 --> 40:05.054
-AFFAIRS ARE SORT
OF CLANDESTINE THINGS

40:05.185 --> 40:07.535
THAT TAKE PLACE
BEHIND CLOSED DOORS.

40:07.666 --> 40:10.408
-WE WANT TO PUT THIS RUMOR
TO REST ONCE AND FOR ALL.

40:20.809 --> 40:23.725
-THE DOORS
ARE OFFICIALLY OPEN.

40:23.856 --> 40:27.555
-I KNEW IT!
I KNEW IT, I KNEW IT.

40:28.208 --> 40:31.429
I'M ALWAYS RIGHT. ALWAYS.

40:51.666 --> 40:57.542
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

41:03.286 --> 41:05.375
-OKAY, MUCHACHOS. LET'S EAT.

41:06.246 --> 41:09.684
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

41:16.648 --> 41:19.259
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
